    </ul>
    <h2>{`General guidelines`}</h2>
    <h3>{`Semantic markup`}</h3>
    <p>{`Always use semantic HTML elements, like `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`button`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ul`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`nav`}</inlineCode>{`. Most modern browsers implement the accessibility features outlined in the specs for these elements; without them, elements will need additional `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/aria"
      }}>{`ARIA attributes and roles`}</a>{` to be recognized by assistive technologies.`}</p>
    <p>{`Elements like `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`h1`}</inlineCode>{`-`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`h6`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`nav`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`footer`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`header`}</inlineCode>{` have `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/aria/roles"
      }}>{`meaningful roles`}</a>{` assigned, so use them, and use them carefully. This can help assistive technologies read the page better and help users find information quicker.`}</p>
    <p>{`Only use a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`div`}</inlineCode>{` or a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`span`}</inlineCode>{` to markup up content when there isn't another HTML element that would semantically be more appropriate, or when an element is needed exclusively for applying CSS styles or JS behaviors.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-html"
      }}>{`<!-- Do: Button can be focused and tabbed to. -->
<button type="button" class="btn">Send</button>
`}</code></pre>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-html"
      }}>{`<!-- Don't: Button can't be focused and tabbed to. -->
<span class="btn">Send</span>
`}</code></pre>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`More on semantic markup:`}</p>
      <ul parentName="blockquote">
        <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
            "href": "http://webaim.org/techniques/semanticstructure/"
